  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7144.52 sitting just below the massive 7150 positive gamma wall (12.2B), dealers are positioned to sell any push higher into that level, creating significant resistance. The PIN regime with 117B in total GEX means dealers will aggressively fade moves - selling the 7150-7200 zone on strength and buying any weakness back toward 7100 support. Watch for mean reversion around current levels as the dense positive gamma walls from 7100-7200 create a stabilizing environment that should contain volatility.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect prices to get pinned between 7100-7150 with dealers capping upside moves.",
